  "title": "Senior Special Education Teacher",
  "description": "<h1>Job Description: Senior Special Education Teacher (Practitioner–Lead)</h1><p>Role Overview<br />The Senior Special Education Teacher is a practitioner–leader who maintains an active teaching role while supervising, mentoring, and managing the education team. Reporting to the Manager for Education / Director for Education & Operations, this role ensures high-quality educational delivery, effective IEP implementation, and compliance with organisational standards through direct instructional practice.<br /><br /></p><h2>Key Responsibilities</h2><p>1. Teaching & Case Management<br />• Maintain an active teaching caseload, including complex and multi-needs learners.<br />• Conduct assessments, lesson planning, intervention delivery, and parent briefings.<br /><br />2. IEP Oversight & Quality Assurance<br />• Lead and review the development, implementation, and revision of IEPs.<br />• Ensure IEPs are evidence-informed, measurable, and aligned with centre frameworks.<br />• Provide guidance and corrective feedback to staff on IEP quality.<br /><br />3. Staff Supervision & Mentorship<br />• Supervise Special Education Teachers, Communication Teachers, and junior staff.<br />• Conduct lesson observations, case discussions, and professional feedback sessions.<br />• Support staff development and succession planning.<br /><br />4. Educational Operations<br />• Oversee daily education operations, lesson quality, and documentation standards.<br />• Identify operational gaps and implement improvements in consultation with management.<br /><br />5. Parent & Stakeholder Communication<br />• Manage complex or escalated parent cases.<br />• Ensure professional, consistent, and appropriate communication practices across the team.<br /><br />6. Programme & Pedagogical Leadership<br />• Lead internal training, research, and development initiatives.<br />• Ensure alignment across special education, communication, and literacy interventions.<br /><br />7. Governance & Compliance<br />• Ensure adherence to ethical standards, PDPA requirements, and internal policies.<br />• Act as a first-line authority for professional conduct and practice standards.<br /><br /></p><h2>Qualifications & Experience</h2><p>• Minimum of 5 years’ experience in Special Education or related fields.</p><p>• Demonstrated experience in supervising or mentoring education professionals.</p><p>• Strong applied knowledge of educational and psychological frameworks.</p><p><br /></p><p><br /></p>",
